## 9. How Authentication Works (Flow Summary)

```
1. sfmc-refresh.ps1 runs (every 15 min via Scheduled Task)
       |
2. Registers a new OAuth client via Dynamic Client Registration
       |
3. Generates PKCE code_verifier + code_challenge (SHA256/S256)
       |
4. Starts HTTP listener on localhost:54321
       |
5. Opens browser to MCP /authorize endpoint
       |
6. MCP server redirects to SFMC login (mc.login.exacttarget.com)
       | (if SFMC session active → auto-completes, no manual login needed)
       |
7. SFMC redirects back to MCP server callback
       |
8. MCP server redirects to localhost:54321/callback?code=...
       |
9. Script captures code, exchanges for Bearer token via /token endpoint
       |
10. Runs: claude mcp remove salesforce-mcp
          claude mcp add --transport http salesforce-mcp {URL} --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
       |
11. MCP server shows: Connected ✅
```

