## 11. SFMC REST API Quirks Discovered (`/data/v1/customobjects`)

These three undocumented quirks caused multiple failures before we cracked them:

### 11.1 Use `length`, NOT `maxLength`
Field property for Text/EmailAddress field length is `length` — not `maxLength`.

```json
{ "name": "SubscriberKey", "type": "Text", "length": 100, "isPrimaryKey": true }
```

Wrong: `"maxLength": 100` → returns `"A text field with no length specified cannot be used as a primary key"` (misleading — the field DOES have length, just under the wrong property name).

### 11.2 EmailAddress type REQUIRES explicit `length`
The API error `"Length is invalid for field EmailAddress because it does not have a data type of Text"` is misleading — it actually means the OPPOSITE: length is **required**, not forbidden.

```json
{ "name": "EmailAddress", "type": "EmailAddress", "length": 254 }   // ✅ works
{ "name": "EmailAddress", "type": "EmailAddress" }                  // ❌ fails
{ "name": "EmailAddress", "type": "EmailAddress", "length": null }  // ❌ fails
{ "name": "EmailAddress", "type": "EmailAddress", "length": 0 }     // ❌ 500 Internal Server Error
{ "type": "Email" }                                                 // ❌ "fieldType is invalid: Email"
```

### 11.3 `sendableSubscriberField` must be a string in PATCH (not an object)
The natural-looking object form throws a deserialization error. PATCH after creating the DE with `isSendable: false`.

```json
// PATCH body — works
{
  "isSendable": true,
  "sendableCustomObjectField": "SubscriberKey",
  "sendableSubscriberField": "Subscriber Key"
}

// Object forms — FAIL with "JSON Deserialization Exception: ... sendableSubscriberField"
{ "sendableSubscriberField": { "name": "Subscriber Key" } }
```

Note: `sendableDataExtensionField` (object form) also works for the DE-side field, but `sendableCustomObjectField` (string) is the canonical name returned by GET.

### 11.4 Required field properties (all booleans, all required on every field)
```
isTemplateField, isHidden, isOverridable, isInheritable, isReadOnly, mustOverride, isNullable
```
Plus: `name`, `type`, `ordinal`. Plus `length` if the type accepts length.

### 11.5 categoryId is required
Look it up via `/email/v1/categories?$filter=categorytype eq 'dataextension'` or use the root DE folder ID. Walk the tree with `parentCatId` to build a path.

